text: Valforêt is a commune in the Côte-d'Or department in eastern France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Clémencey (the seat) and Quemigny-Poisot.Arrêté préfectoral 21 November 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Côte-d'Or department ==References== Category:Communes of Côte-d'Or Category:Populated places established in 2019
title: Valforêt
